        java.util.List<WishlistItem> getProductsByKeyword​(java.lang.String keyword)
                                           throws java.io.IOException
        Method for retrieving the products offered by a vendor that match a certain keyword
        Parameters:
        keyword - the text to search the products for
        Returns:
        a List containing products that match the keyword
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if retrieving the information from the vendor's website fails (e.g. the website does not respond)

      • computePrice

        double computePrice​(WishlistItem item)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Method for computing the price dynamically of a product, by accessing its dedicated page on the vendor's website. This method should only be called when a user requests to access their wishlist, in order to provide the current price for each product.
        Parameters:
        item - the item to compute the price for
        Returns:
        the current price for the item
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if retrieving the information from the vendor's website fails (e.g. the website does not respond)
